Display wiring for ESP32 Audio Kit V2.2

Display pin   -> ESP32 Audio Kit pin
-----------------------------------
VCC           -> 3V3
GND           -> GND
DIN (MOSI)    -> GPIO23
CLK (SCLK)    -> GPIO18
CS            -> GPIO5
DC            -> GPIO19
RST           -> RST
BL            -> GPIO22

Notes:
- Use the ESP32 3.3V rail for VCC. Do not connect VCC to 5V.
- Make sure GND is shared between the display and the ESP32 board.
- RST is connected to the module reset pin so the display can reset with the ESP32.
- BL is the display backlight enable pin and should be powered/enabled for a visible image.
- This wiring matches the pin definitions used in `src/esp32_main.cpp` and `include/User_Setup.h`.